node.text:
What a week. What an experience. 
⚾️🤩💯
Bentley got invited to play in the 12U Perfect Game the Series Classic baseball tourney in Fort Myers, Florida. 12 year olds from all over made up 14 different U.S. teams, with the other 4 teams made of kids from the Dominican Republic, Puerto Rico and Venezuela. 

He spent a week with boys from all over the world! An extra bonus his team made it to the final 4, knocking off the #1 seed in the process. He spent time getting to know kids from other travel ball teams. He talked and competed with baseball players from other countries. He hit off of multiple kids pitching 77-80 mph and pitched to kids that hit home runs out of major league stadiums. He made memories this week he will never forget! 

He had a teammate from the Dominican Republic that did not speak English, who was given #85 (Bentley’s Original Number). By the end of the week they learned how to communicate with each other! 😌

What. A. Time.
 #TeamMidAtlantic #thingsthatmatter

node.text:
Benny's first middle school wrestling experience. He was so nervous and excited, it was all this kid talked about all week. He won both matches! 

"That was SO MUCH FUN," was the first thing he said to me when we got in the car. He spent most of the car ride home bragging about his teammates and their matches, and he talked about the strong bond that they have.

I'm so thankful to be back with our wrestling family, and that Benny has amazing kids as teammates and brothers.

#bucswrestling #thingsthatmatter #panther

node.text:
What a week. What an experience. 
⚾️🤩💯
Bentley got invited to play in the 12U Perfect Game the Series Classic baseball tourney in Fort Myers, Florida. 12 year olds from all over made up 14 different U.S. teams, with the other 4 teams made of kids from the Dominican Republic, Puerto Rico and Venezuela. 

He spent a week with boys from all over the world! An extra bonus his team made it to the final 4, knocking off the #1 seed in the process. He spent time getting to know kids from other travel ball teams. He talked and competed with baseball players from other countries. He hit off of multiple kids pitching 77-80 mph and pitched to kids that hit home runs out of major league stadiums. He made memories this week he will never forget! 

He had a teammate from the Dominican Republic that did not speak English, who was given #85 (Bentley’s Original Number). By the end of the week they learned how to communicate with each other! 😌

What. A. Time.
 #TeamMidAtlantic #thingsthatmatter
